summary:
Aliaris gets a step further and is completly remade from scratch, and comes in with Ambient Occlusion

No screenshot because I try to make them without steam XD, seriously. its overlay is annoying!
descriptionHtml:
Aliaris ENB:
vibrant, lush, yet natural colors and light. Bright days, realistic shadows. Cozy Inns, homes, and shops.
Low illuminated nights, close to "really dark". pitch black caves, dungeons, tunnels or bandit hideouts, only illumiated by fires, candles or your torch.
Aliaris makes each frame worth an screenshot.


-----------------------------------------

Offering unique lens reflections and flares.
ambient occlusion and depth of field
subtle filmgrain effect

----------------------------------------------

REQUIREMENTS_
132 binary files from enbdev.com
http://enbdev.com/mod_tesskyrim_v0132.htm
skyrimprefs: bfloatpointrendertarget
-----------------------------------------------

Recommended:
enhanced camera (best first person EVER!!!)
http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/55738/?



texture mod used in screenshots:
rugged rocks
http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/6225/?

my system
intel i5 quadcore clock 3.4 GHz
Nvidia Geforce GTX 745 ( guess it was 4 GB Memory... ?)
12 GB DR3 RAM
getting between 28 - 45 frames with the enb settings like in that dl.
all skyrim setting on highest level (vanilla ini - non-tweaked skyrim prefs)
